    </ul>

    <h2>FAQs</h2>
    <div class="faq">
        <h3>Is Butcher BBQ Prime Barbecue Brisket Injection suitable for other meats?</h3>
        <p>Yes, while it’s specifically designed for brisket, you can also use it on other cuts of meat like pork butt, turkey, or even chicken. The injection will add moisture and flavor to any meat you choose to use it on.</p>

        <h3>How much injection should I use per pound of brisket?</h3>
        <p>The general rule of thumb is to use about 1 ounce of injection per pound of brisket. However, you can adjust the amount based on your personal preference and the size of the brisket.</p>

        <h3>Can I use this injection if I’m on a gluten-free diet?</h3>
        <p>Absolutely! Butcher BBQ Prime Barbecue Brisket Injection is gluten-free, making it a safe choice for those with gluten sensitivities or celiac disease.</p>

        <h3>Do I need to let the brisket rest after injecting?</h3>
        <p>It’s a good idea to let the brisket rest for at least 30 minutes after injecting. This allows the flavors to penetrate the meat more deeply and ensures even distribution of the injection.</p>
